FBIS3-22078 "jptdd013__l94081" JPRS-tdd-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 9 February 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA PAKISTAN Agreement Signed With Iran To Counter Drug Smuggling 94WD0252G Karachi AMN in Urdu 9 Feb 94 p 8 94WD0252G Karachi AMN Language: Urdu Article Type:CSO [News Report: "Pakistan-Iran Agreement on Eradicating Drug Smuggling"] [Text] Islamabad, 8 February (TV Report)--Pakistan and Iran have expressed agreement to end drug smuggling and have closer relations. This agreement was reached after a three-day meeting of a special Iran-Pakistan committee in Islamabad. Iran's minister of political and social affairs, Ali Reza Tabish, and Pakistan's secretary of internal affairs, Jamshed Barki, signed this agreement today and during their talks exchanged ideas about increasing trade and communication across the border.
